---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "What is the New 2026 Tournament Format? 48 Teams Explained",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "hammaadworks"
  },
  "datePublished": "2026-06-05",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "cupcal"
  }
};

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How many teams are in the 2026 tournament?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The 2026 global tournament features 48 teams, an expansion from the traditional 32-team format used in previous editions."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How many matches are in the 2026 tournament?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "There are a total of 104 matches in the 2026 tournament, resulting from the expansion to 48 teams and the introduction of a new Round of 32 knockout stage."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout title="What is the New 2026 Tournament Format? 48 Teams Explained" description="A complete breakdown of the new 48-team, 104-match format for the 2026 global tournament in North America.">
  <main class="py-20 container px-4 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <a href="/blog" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 mb-8 inline-block font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm border border-indigo-500/30 px-4 py-2 rounded-full backdrop-blur-sm">← Back to Guides</a>
    
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg lg:prose-xl max-w-none prose-headings:font-black prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-indigo-400">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-white mb-6 leading-tight drop-shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(255,255,255,0.2)]" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">
        What is the New 2026 Tournament Format? (48 Teams Explained)
      </h1>
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-slate-400 mb-12 font-medium border-b border-white/10 pb-6">
        <span>By hammaadworks</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>June 5, 2026</span>
      </div>

      <p class="lead text-2xl text-slate-300 font-medium">
        The 2026 edition marks the biggest structural change in the history of international football. The tournament is expanding from 32 to 48 teams, drastically altering how the group stage and knockout rounds operate.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">The Core Numbers: 2026 vs 2022</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        To understand the scale of this expansion, we have to look at the raw data. The 2026 tournament introduces a massive 40-match increase over the previous edition.
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-slate-300 border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10 bg-white/5 text-white">
              <th class="p-4 font-bold">Metric</th>
              <th class="p-4 font-bold">Previous Format (32 Teams)</th>
              <th class="p-4 font-bold text-indigo-300">New 2026 Format (48 Teams)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="p-4 font-medium text-white">Total Matches</td>
              <td class="p-4">64</td>
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-indigo-300">104</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="p-4 font-medium text-white">Groups</td>
              <td class="p-4">8 groups of 4</td>
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-indigo-300">12 groups of 4</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4 font-medium text-white">Knockout Stage Starts At</td>
              <td class="p-4">Round of 16</td>
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-indigo-300">Round of 32</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">How Does the Group Stage Work?</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        The 48 teams are divided into <strong>12 groups (A through L)</strong>, with 4 teams in each group. Every team plays three group stage matches, just like in previous tournaments.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        The biggest change is how teams advance. Out of the 48 teams, 32 will advance to the knockout rounds:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 marker:text-indigo-500">
        <li>The <strong>top two teams</strong> from each of the 12 groups automatically advance (24 teams).</li>
        <li>The <strong>8 best third-place teams</strong> across all groups also advance, creating a highly competitive scramble on the final day of the group stages.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl text-white mt-12 mb-6">The New Round of 32</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        Because 32 teams now advance instead of 16, a brand new knockout round has been introduced: the <strong>Round of 32</strong>. 
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        This means that to win the entire tournament, the champions will have to play <strong>8 matches</strong> instead of the traditional 7. The total length of the tournament has been extended to 39 days to accommodate this additional round and ensure players get adequate rest between fixtures.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-16 p-8 bg-indigo-900/30 border border-indigo-500/30 rounded-3xl backdrop-blur-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="text-2xl">💡</span> Quick Summary for Fans
        </h3>
        <p class="text-indigo-200 mb-0">
          More teams mean more matches (104 total). Your team now needs to survive a 12-group gauntlet and an extra knockout round (the Round of 32) to lift the trophy in New York/New Jersey on July 19, 2026.
        </p>
      </div>

    </article>
  </main>
  
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
</BaseLayout>
